      "description": "Offering a museum-grade 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, a pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering. This example features the legendary 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine, showing no signs of housing wear or apex seal degradation. The vacuum-actuated boost control system is perfectly calibrated, ensuring a seamless transition between the primary and secondary Hitachi HT12 turbos. The chassis retains its factory-spec 50/50 weight distribution and lightweight aluminum double-wishbone suspension, providing exceptional transient response. This R1-package unit includes the original dual oil coolers and Z-rated tire specified springs. The five-speed manual transmission shifts with mechanical precision, paired with a chatter-free Torsen limited-slip differential. Zero aftermarket modifications; original paint and interior remain in impeccable, preserved state.",
